They are not calibrated equally, so you cannot compare your score on one of these machines, as they are not calibrated the same. And every manufacturer makes machines that spit out completely different numbers. There are brakes in the lever arm. If you don't hit it in exactly the right direction, the brakes kick in. These machines are DESIGNED to be inaccurate. 5 guys walk up to an accurate machine, they each pay for one turn, and find out who hits hardest.
